<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Burlingame</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 62.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-05"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 5, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            been so fortunate as to secure the recognition, by the Chinese
                            government, of the rights of Sweden under a treaty negotiated at Canton
                            in 1847, and to forward the kind letter of Mr. Cunningham, marked A,
                            acknowledging that service.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>ANSON BURLINGAME.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <head>A.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of Sweden and
                                            Norway</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Shanghai,</hi></placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-04"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 4, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your excellency’s letter of November 7, and to thank you
                                for your very successful effort to procure from the Chinese high
                                authorities the recognition of my official position under the treaty
                                with Sweden, negotiated at Canton in, 1847.</p>
                            <p>I shall report to the government at Stockholm the very kind
                                assistance you have rendered, as evincing the friendly feeling
                                entertained by you towards Swedish interests in China.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>EDWARD CUNNINGHAM, <hi rend="italic">Acting Consul
                                        General.</hi></signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>His Excellency Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>